<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;;PADDING:0PT 3.35PT 0PT 0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Approval of the annual budget of the Company
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 5.55PT 0PT 0PT;">
	7.3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Procedure
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 6.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Board must appoint a chairperson from among its members, and may choose a secretary who need not be a director and who will be responsible for keeping the minutes of the meetings of the Board and of General Meetings.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 4.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Board meets at the request of the chairperson or the majority of the Board of directors, at the place indicated in the notice, which in principle is in Luxembourg.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 2.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(iii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Written notice of any Board meeting is given to all directors at least twenty-four (24)&nbsp;&nbsp;hours in advance, except in the case of an emergency whose nature and circumstances are set forth in the notice.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 2.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(iv)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	No notice is required if all members of the Board are present or represented and state that they know the agenda for the meeting. A director may also waive notice of a meeting, either before or after the meeting. Separate written notices are not required for meetings which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	are held at times and places indicated in a schedule previously adopted by the Board.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 3.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(v)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	A director may grant another director a power of attorney in order to be represented at any Board meeting.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 2.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(vi)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Board may only validly deliberate and act if a majority of its members are present or represented. Board Resolutions are validly adopted if the majority of the members of the Board vote in their favour. The chairman has a casting vote in the event of a tie vote. Board resolutions are recorded in minutes signed by the chairperson, by all directors present or represented at the meeting, or by the secretary (if any).
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 113.9PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(vii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Any director may participate in any meeting of the Board by telephone or video conference, or by any other means of communication which allows all those taking part in the meeting to identify, hear and speak to each other. Participation by such means is deemed equivalent to participation in person at a duly convened and held meeting .
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	Circular resolutions signed by all the directors (the

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 2.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(ix)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	A director who has an interest in a transaction carried out other than in the ordinary course of business which conflicts with the interests of the Company must advise the Board accordingly and have the statement recorded in the minutes of the meeting. The director concerned may not take part in the deliberations concerning that transaction. A special report on the relevant transaction is submitted to the shareholders at the next General Meeting, before any vote on the matter.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 5.55PT 0PT 0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Representation

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 6.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Company is bound towards third parties in all matters by the joint signature of the majority of the Board.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:19PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 4.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Company is also bound towards third parties by the joint or single signature of any person to whom special signatory powers have been delegated.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;;PADDING:0PT 5.55PT 0PT 0PT;">
	8.1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Where the number of shareholders is reduced to one (1), the Company may be managed by a single director until the ordinary General Meeting following the introduction of an additional shareholder. In this case, any reference in the Articles to the Board or the directors should be read as a reference to that sole director, as appropriate.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

Notwithstanding the foregoing, the current or former director or officer will not be entitled to indemnification in
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Furthermore, in case of settlement, the current or former director or officer will only be entitled to indemnification hereunder, provided that (i) the Board shall have determined in good faith that the defendant's actions did not constitute willful and deliberate violations of the law and shall have obtained the relevant legal advice to that effect; and (ii) notice of the intention of settlement of such action, suit or proceeding is given to the Company at least 10 business days prior to such settlement.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;(i)Resolutions of the shareholders are adopted at a general meeting of shareholders (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	). The General Meeting has full powers to adopt and ratify all acts and operations which are consistent with the company&#x2019;s corporate object.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

	(ii)Each share gives entitlement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	to one (1) vote.
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;">

<TD STYLE="WIDTH:7PT;">

</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Notices, quorum, majority and voting proceedings
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(i)General Meetings are held at the time and place specified in the notices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(ii)The notices for any ordinary General Meeting or extraordinary General Meeting shall contain the agenda, the hour and the place of the meeting and shall be made by notices published twice (2) at least at eight (8) days interval and eight (8) days before the meeting in the Memorial C, Recueil des Soci&#xE9;t&#xE9;s et Associations (Luxembourg Official Gazette) and in a leading newspaper having general circulation in Luxembourg. In case the shares of the Company are listed on a foreign regulated market, the notices shall, in addition, (subject to applicable regulations) either (i) be published once in a leading newspaper having general circulation in the country of such listing at the same time as the first publication in Luxembourg or (ii) follow the market practices in such country regarding publicity of the convening of a general meeting of shareholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(iii)If all the shareholders are present or represented and consider themselves duly convened and informed of the agenda, the General Meeting may be held without prior notice.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(iv)A shareholder may grant written power of attorney to another person, shareholder or otherwise, in order to be represented at any General Meeting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(v)Any shareholder may participate in any General Meeting by telephone or video conference, or by any other means of communication which allows all those taking part in the meeting to identify, hear and speak to each other. Participation by such means is deemed equivalent to participation in person at the meeting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage114"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(vi)Any shareholder may vote by using the forms provided to that effect by the Company. Voting forms contain the date, place and agenda of the meeting and the text of the proposed resolutions. For each resolution, the form must contain three boxes allowing for a vote for or against that resolution or an abstention. Shareholders must return the voting forms to the registered office. Only voting forms received prior to the General Meeting are taken into account for calculation of the quorum. Forms which indicate neither a voting intention nor an abstention are void.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(vii)Resolutions of the General Meeting are passed by a simple majority vote, regardless of the proportion of share capital represented.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(viii) An extraordinary General Meeting (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Extraordinary General Meeting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) may only amend the Articles if at least one-half of the share capital is represented and the agenda indicates the proposed amendments to the Articles, including the text of any proposed amendment to the Company&#x2019;s object or form. If this quorum is not reached, a second Extraordinary General Meeting may be convened by means of notices published twice in the M&#xE9;morial and two Luxembourg newspapers, at an interval of at fifteen (15) days and fifteen (15) days before the meeting. These notices state the date and agenda of the Extraordinary General Meeting and the results of the previous Extraordinary General Meeting. The second Extraordinary General Meeting deliberates validly regardless of the proportion of capital represented. At both Extraordinary General Meetings, resolutions must be adopted by at least two-thirds of the votes cast.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(ix)Any change in the nationality of the Company and any increase in a shareholder&#x2019;s commitment in the Company require the unanimous consent of the shareholders and bondholders (if any).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:13.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Art. 12.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
	Procedure
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:25.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
	Every General Meeting will be presided over by the chairman pro tempore appointed by the General Meeting. The General Meeting will appoint a scrutineer who shall keep the attendance list.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:25.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
	The board of the General Meeting so constituted shall designate the secretary.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:25.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
	Irrespective of the agenda, the Board may adjourn any ordinary General Meeting or Extraordinary General Meeting in accordance with the formalities and time limits stipulated for by law.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:25.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
	Minutes of the General Meetings shall be signed by the members of the board of the meeting. Copies or excerpts of the minutes to be produced in court or elsewhere shall be signed by two (2) directors or by the secretary of the Board or by any assistant secretary.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	13. Sole shareholder
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	13.1When the number of shareholders is reduced to one (1), the sole shareholder exercises all powers granted by the Law to the General Meeting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	13.2Any reference to the General Meeting in the Articles is to be read as a reference to the sole shareholder, as appropriate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	9
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage115"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	13.3The resolutions of the sole shareholder are recorded in minutes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
	v.ANNUAL
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ACCOUNTS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
	- ALLOCATION OF PROFITS - SUPERVISION
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	14.Financial year and approval of annual accounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	14.1The financial year begins on 1 January and ends on 31 December of each year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	14.2The Board prepares the balance sheet and profit and loss account annually, together with as an inventory stating the value of the Company&#x2019;s assets and liabilities, with an annex summarising its commitments and the debts owed by its officers, directors and statutory auditors to the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	14.3One month before the Annual General Meeting, the Board provides the statutory auditors with a report on and documentary evidence of the Company&#x2019;s operations. The statutory auditors then prepare a report stating their findings and proposals.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	14.4The Annual General Meeting is held at the registered office or in any other place within the municipality of the registered office, as specified in the notice, on the fourth Tuesday in May at 10 a.m. If that day is a public holiday or the day following a public holiday in the United States of America, the Annual General Meeting shall be held on the Tuesday of the following week.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	14.5The annual General Meeting may be held abroad if, in the Board&#x2019;s, absolute and final judgement, exceptional circumstances so require.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	15.Auditors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	15.1The Company&#x2019;s operations are supervised by one or more statutory auditors (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	commissaires
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	15.2When so required by law, or when the Company so chooses, the Company&#x2019;s operations are supervised by one or more approved external auditors (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	r&#xE9;viseurs d&#x2019;entreprises agr&#xE9;&#xE9;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	15.3The General Meeting appoints the statutory auditors (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	commissaires
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	) / external auditors (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	r&#xE9;viseurs d&#x2019;entreprises agr&#xE9;&#xE9;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	), and determines their number and&nbsp;&nbsp;remuneration and the term of their mandate, which may not exceed six (6) years but may be renewed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	16.Allocation of profits
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	16.1Five per cent (5%) of the Company&#x2019;s annual net profits are allocated to the reserve required by law. This requirement ceases when the legal reserve reaches an amount equal to ten per cent (10%) of the share capital.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	16.2The General Meeting determines the allocation of the balance of the annual net profits. They may decide on the payment of a dividend, to transfer the balance to a reserve account, or to carry it forward in accordance with the applicable legal provisions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	16.3Interim dividends may be distributed at any time, under the following conditions:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(i)the Board draws up interim accounts;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	10
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">

	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage116"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:32.2689075630252%;MARGIN-RIGHT:4.70588235294118%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(ii)the interim accounts show that sufficient profits and other reserves (including share premiums) are available for distribution; it being understood that the amount to be distributed may not exceed the profits made since the end of the last financial year for which the annual accounts have been approved, if any, increased by profits carried forward and distributable reserves, and reduced by losses carried forward and sums to be allocated to the legal or a statutory reserve;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(iii)the decision to distribute interim dividends is made by the Board within two (2) months from the date of the interim accounts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	In their report to the Board, the statutory auditors (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	commissaires
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	) &nbsp;or the approved external auditors &nbsp;(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	r&#xE9;viseurs d&#x2019;entreprises agr&#xE9;&#xE9;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	), as applicable, must verify whether the above conditions have been satisfied.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	16.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company may make payment of dividends and any other payments in cash, shares or other securities to a Depositary. Said Depositary shall distribute these funds to his depositors according to the amount of securities or other financial instruments recorded in their name. Such payment by the Company to the Depositary will effect full discharge of the Company&#x2019;s obligations in this regard.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;;PADDING:0PT 3.45PT 0PT 0PT;">
	VI.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	DISSOLUTION &#x2013; LIQUIDATION
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	17.1The Company may be dissolved at any time by a resolution of the General Meeting, acting in accordance with the conditions prescribed for the amendment of the Articles. The General Meeting appoints one or more liquidators, who need not be shareholders, to carry out the liquidation, and determines their number, powers and remuneration. Unless otherwise decided by the General Meeting, the liquidators have full powers to realise the Company&#x2019;s assets and pay its liabilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	17.2The surplus after realisation of the assets and payment of the liabilities is distributed to the shareholders in proportion to the shares held by each of them.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:6.5PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:5.1PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
	VII.General provision
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	18.1Notices and communications may be made or waived and circular resolutions may be evidenced in writing, fax, email or any other means of electronic communication.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	18.2Powers of attorney are granted by any of the means described above. Powers of attorney in connection with Board meetings may also be granted by a director, in accordance with such conditions as may be accepted by the Board.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL,HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	18.3Signatures may be in handwritten or electronic form, provided they fulfil all legal requirements for being deemed equivalent to handwritten signatures. Signatures of circular resolutions or resolutions adopted by telephone or video conference are affixed to one original or several counterparts of the same document, all of which taken together constitute one and the same document.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:17.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.85PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;(x)&nbsp;the aggregate amount of cash previously provided under Section&nbsp;16 that (i)&nbsp;has not been released and (ii)&nbsp;constitutes Collateral with a perfected Lien in favor of the Security Agent as of such date and (y)&nbsp;the fair market value (as reasonably determined by the Security Agent acting in good faith) of any non-cash security (other than a Collateral Vessel) previously provided under Section&nbsp;16 that (i)&nbsp;has not been released and (ii)&nbsp;constitutes Collateral with a perfected Lien in favor of the Security Agent as of such date.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:72PT;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#010000;">
	SECTION&nbsp;2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Prepayment and Cash Collateral Release
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;The parties hereto hereby agree that:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:72PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;COLOR:#010000;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Within 2 Business Days of written notice to the Borrowers from the Administrative Agent (which notice may be given at any time during the 14 Business Day period beginning on the Amendment Effective Date), the Obligors shall instruct the Security Agent to transfer an amount equal to $31,695,092.45 from PDSA&#x2019;s cash collateral account to the Administrative Agent (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Cash Collateral Release
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;) to be applied in full towards the partial discharge of the next occurring semi-annual principal installment required to be made pursuant to each of Sections&nbsp;8.1 and 8.2 of the Credit Agreement, pro rata between the Commercial Facility Tranche and the GIEK Facility Tranche. &nbsp;If such notice is not given by the Administrative Agent as aforesaid, the Borrowers may elect to instruct the Security Agent to effect the Cash Collateral Release on or about the date on which the next semi-annual principal installment is required to be made pursuant to either of Sections&nbsp;8.1 and 8.2 of the Credit Agreement, for application of the full amount of the Cash Collateral Release towards the partial discharge of that semi-annual principal installment. &nbsp;It shall be an Event of Default if, after notice given by the Administrative Agent as described above, the Obligors fail to issue instructions to cause the Cash Collateral Release within 2 Business Days after receipt of such notice by the Borrowers.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Notwithstanding Sections&nbsp;13.8(g)&nbsp;and 16.3 of the Credit Agreement, after giving effect to this Amendment and the making of the Prepayment, no additional security or prepayment is required pursuant to Sections&nbsp;13.8(g)&nbsp;and 16.3 of the Credit Agreement and no Default or Event of Default shall be deemed to have arisen under Section&nbsp;13.8(g)&nbsp;of the Credit Agreement as a result of the Fair Market Value of the Collateral Vessels based upon the valuations of such Collateral Vessels delivered to the Administrative Agent, dated as of December&nbsp;31, 2016.

Delivery of an executed counterpart of a signature page&nbsp;to this Amendment by telecopier shall be effective as delivery of a manually executed counterpart of this Amendment.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is limited precisely as written and shall not be deemed to (i) be a waiver of or a consent to the modification of or deviation from any other term or condition of the Credit Agreement or the other Credit Documents or any of the other instruments or agreements referred to therein, or (ii) prejudice any right or rights which any of the Lenders or the Administrative Agent now have or may have in the future under or in connection with the Credit Agreement, as amended hereby, the other Credit Documents or any of the other instruments or agreements referred to therein.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Borrower confirms and agrees that the Credit Agreement and each of the Security Documents to which it is a party is and shall continue to be in full force and effect and is ratified and confirmed in all respects, except that, on and after the
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	Each of the parties hereto hereby irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction and venue of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York and of any New York State court sitting in New York County, Borough of Manhattan, and any appellate court from any such federal or state court, for purposes of all suits, actions or legal proceedings arising out of or relating to this Sixth Amendment and the Credit Agreement or the transactions contemplated hereby or thereby.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each of the parties hereto irrevocably waives, to the fullest extent permitted by law, any objection that it may now or hereafter have to the laying of the venue of any such proceeding brought in such a court and any claim that any such proceeding brought in such a court has been brought in an inconvenient forum.&nbsp;&nbsp;EACH OF THE BORROWER, THE ADMINISTRATIVE AGENT AND THE LENDERS PARTY HERETO HEREBY IRREVOCABLY WAIVES ALL RIGHT TO TRIAL BY JURY IN ANY ACTION, PROCEEDING OR COUNTERCLAIM (WHETHER BASED ON CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE) ARISING OUT OF OR RELATING TO THIS SIXTH AMENDMENT, THE&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;15.1
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CONSENT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Board of Directors
<BR />
	Pacific Drilling S.A.:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We consent to the incorporation by reference in the registration statements (No. 333-180485 and No. 333-194380) on Form S-8 of Pacific Drilling S.A. of our report dated February 24, 2017, with respect to the consolidated balance sheets of Pacific Drilling S.A. and subsidiaries (the Company) as of December&nbsp;31, 2016 and 2015, and the related consolidated statements of operations, comprehensive income, shareholders&#x2019; equity, and cash flows for each of the years in the three-year period ended December&nbsp;31, 2016, which report appears in the December&nbsp;31, 2016 annual report on Form 20-F of Pacific Drilling S.A.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our report contains an explanatory paragraph that states that the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	expects to be in violation of certain of its financial covenants in the next 12 months, which raises substantial doubt about its ability to continue as a going concern.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The consolidated financial statements do not include any adjustments that might result from the outcome of that uncertainty.
</FONT>
</P>
